-- QSR Slumps Most in 32 Months After Rejecting Carlyle's $614 Million Offer
-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 2010-11-30T01:09:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/qsr-slumps-most-in-32-months-after-rejecting-carlyle-s-614-million-offer.html
QSR Brands Bhd. fell the most in 32
months after parent Kulim (Malaysia) Bhd. rejected a 1.94
billion ringgit ($614 million) takeover bid from Carlyle Group
and a matching rival offer for the Southeast Asian fast-food
chain operator.  The shares slid 7.7 percent to 5.78 ringgit at 9:02 a.m. in
Kuala Lumpur trading, set for its steepest decline since March
10, 2008. Kulim dropped 3.2 percent to 11.70 ringgit. KFC
Holdings (Malaysia) Bhd., controlled by QSR, slid 3.6 percent to
3.80 ringgit.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chan Tien Hin at 
 thchan@bloomberg.net  